OL,6,FMr Mewse was given a 12-week suspended
OL,7,Fsentence and ordered to pay costs of
OL,8,F#804.JTo further protect the victim,
OL,9,Fhe was also issued with a two-year
OL,10,Frestraining order.JSibylle Cheruvier,
OL,11,Fa District Crown Prosecutor with CPS
OL,12,FWessex said, "Mark Mewes pursued a
OL,13,Fdeliberate campaign of harassment
OL,14,Fagainst his victim after their
OL,15,Frelationship ended. "The victim was
OL,16,Fquite clear that his behaviour was
OL,17,Funwelcome, however these pleas were
OL,18,Fignored in favour of his own selfish
OL,19,Finterests. "His conduct was nothing
OL,20,Fshort of criminal and I hope that his
OL,21,Fconviction sends the message that the
OL,22,FCPS takes harassment extremely
OL,23,Fseriously.J"I would like to commend
OL,24,Fthe victim for coming forward and
OL,25,Fsupporting our prosecution. I hope
OL,26,Fthis successful result goes some way
